The Yakmun clan, which boasted a long time ago, was wiped out in a massacre. The corpses piled up like mountains, and the blood flooded everything like ocean water. Amidst this hell of despair, Sura, opened his eyes: "No one shall be spared. I shall kill everyone. It doesn't end unless I've killed each and every one of them."
Jin Ja-Kang was the lone survivor, and with him a man's lonely revenge, which will be recorded as a legend in the Murimsa Temple in the future, begins!
(Source: KakaoPage, translated)

Estio is just an ordinary farmer’s son, but with an extraordinary ability—he can read the thoughts and memories of humans and animals. For this, he is shunned by the people in his village, finding happiness only in his animal friends. After years of silently enduring the villagers’ hostility, Estio runs away the night he turns 19. His journey brings unexpected friendships and encounters, but will such bonds be able to show him there is more to him and his ability than meets the eye?
(Source: Tapas)
